==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From the Greek prefix '''[[mega-]]''' "large", plus Japanese [[津波]] / [[津浪]] (つなみ, tsunami), "harbour wave"

===Pronunciation===
*mega-tso͞o-nä'mi, {{IPAchar|/mɛgə-tsuːˈnɑːmi/}}, /<tt>mEg&-tsu:nA:mi</tt>/
*mega-so͞o-nä'mi, {{IPAchar|/mɛgə-suːˈnɑːmi/}}, /<tt>mEg&-su:nA:mi</tt>/

===Noun===
'''megatsunami''' (''Plural:'' '''megatsunamis''' ''or'' '''megatsunami''')

# A '''megatsunami''' is a term used by the popular media to describe very large [[tsunami]]s, which are very large and destructive [[wave]]s that are generally caused by a tremendous disturbance in the ocean floor. The term '''megatsunami''' is used informally for tsunamis with wave heights of 40 m or greater.

